  <prompt>
    Scaffold the EmailComposer Code Page directory at `src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/`, mirroring the file layout of `src/client/code-pages/DocumentRelationshipViewer/`. Create the skeleton ONLY — do not mount `<EmailComposer />` yet (task 033 does the mount). The goal is a deployable, empty-shell Code Page that builds and serves a "Hello" page so tasks 031–034 can iterate on auth, URL parsing, and the wrapper mount independently.

    Files to create: `src/main.tsx` (or `src/index.tsx` per exemplar), `src/App.tsx` (minimal shell), `src/auth/` placeholder directory, `index.html`, `vite.config.ts` (or `webpack.config.js` matching exemplar's bundler), `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `build-webresource.ps1`. Choose the bundler that matches the canonical exemplar.

    Verify the scaffold builds locally before completing.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke frontend engineer. Familiar with the Code Page architecture per ADR-026 and the `code-page-deploy` skill. Has read the DocumentRelationshipViewer exemplar end-to-end.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new directory `src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/` containing the same file scaffold as `DocumentRelationshipViewer/` (sans the visualization-specific components). `npm install` succeeds. `npm run build` (or equivalent) produces a deployable artifact even though the App.tsx body is a placeholder.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The EmailComposer Code Page is the canonical Surface 2 entry point (Form Component Control replacement for `sprk_communication`) and Surface 1 entry point (ribbon "+ New Email"). Per FR-18 it deploys as the Dataverse web resource `sprk_emailcomposer`. Wave 1 ships the `<SendEmailPage />` wrapper this Code Page will eventually mount (task 033); Wave 2 builds the host.

      Per the empirical findings in `CLAUDE.md`, the exemplar is at `src/client/code-pages/DocumentRelationshipViewer/` (22 files including auth, types, components, services, build script). This task replicates the structure WITHOUT yet wiring the email-specific logic.
    </background>
