  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read DocumentRelationshipViewer exemplar files: `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `webpack.config.js`, `index.html`, `src/index.tsx`, `src/App.tsx`, `build-webresource.ps1`. Note bundler choice (webpack vs vite) and follow it.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/` directory.</step>
    <step order="3">Copy + adapt `package.json` — change `name` to `emailcomposer-code-page`, version `0.1.0`, scripts match exemplar.</step>
    <step order="4">Copy + adapt `tsconfig.json` — keep as-is (paths relative to new dir).</step>
    <step order="5">Copy + adapt bundler config (`webpack.config.js` or `vite.config.ts`) — adjust entry/output paths for the new directory.</step>
    <step order="6">Copy + adapt `index.html` — title "Email Composer", placeholder root div `<div id="root"></div>`.</step>
    <step order="7">Create `src/index.tsx` — React 18 `createRoot` calling `<App />` (mirror exemplar's entry shape).</step>
    <step order="8">Create `src/App.tsx` — minimal placeholder rendering "Email Composer (scaffold)" inside Fluent v9 `<FluentProvider theme={webLightTheme}>`. NO `<EmailComposer />` or `<SendEmailPage />` mount yet.</step>
    <step order="9">Create empty placeholder directory `src/auth/` (or `src/services/auth/` matching exemplar) with a README marker file noting "Wired in task 031".</step>
    <step order="10">Copy + adapt `build-webresource.ps1` — target web resource name `sprk_emailcomposer`; output path correct for the new dir.</step>
    <step order="11">Run `npm install` in the new directory; confirm zero errors.</step>
    <step order="12">Run `npm run build` (or exemplar's prod build script); confirm artifact emitted to expected output path.</step>
    <step order="13">Verify with `Get-ChildItem` / `dir` that the directory layout matches the exemplar's file set (sans email-specific extras).</step>
    <step order="14">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 030 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="15">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed; advance to next pending task (031).</step>
  </steps>

